rector of retail at choice food group where he was responsible for all aspects of the retail division including accounting financial analysis marketing management operations and purchasing as well as vendor and customer relations  in addition he was responsible for identifying and executing projects for the retail division as well as for choice food group’s distribution and manufacturing divisions  in  after close to five years with choice food group phil started incrowd capital an online fundraising platform that combines his previous experiences in finance with his passion for business and entrepreneurship  eric grigorian founder alabama incrowd llclinkedineric has been living in huntsville alabama since  and calls huntsville home  he is  and  graduate of the university of alabama in huntsville with bachelor and masters of science degrees in electrical engineering respectively  he has over  years of experience in design development integration technical management and operations in aerospace defense and commercial industrieseric started his professional career at intergraph corporation during his fourteenyear service he gained valuable experience in several engineering disciplines which included commercial and defense programs  as an executive technical manager at intergraph he was responsible for the initiation product development and integration of rugged cotsbased workstations for naval applications that even todate are still being maintained and supported  eric has been engaged in several startups in alabama which include applied data trends mole town qpc and arkitrol and has served as chief engineer vice president of product development and chief operating officer  at applied data trends he was awarded for assisting with growth of the company which was recognized by inc magazine as one of the top  fastest growing companies  at qpc a company that was a pioneer in producing computing and telematics components for aftermarket and recreational vehicles and was recognized at consumer electronics show in the new product category eric served as the coo and vice president of product development  additionally he has been active member of numerous professional organizations and has served as advisor and board member for several nonprofit organizationseric has received numerous awards and recognitions including  ieee region  southeast us outstanding engineer  ieeehuntsville section professional of the year and  uah distinguished young engineering alumni incrowd capitals advisory team  dr jeff cornwallinaugural jack c massey chair in entrepreneurship and professor of entrepreneurship  belmont universitydr jeff cornwall is the inaugural recipient of the jack c massey chair in entrepreneurship and professor of entrepreneurship at belmont university in nashville tennessee  he has a doctorate in business administration and an mba from the university of kentucky   in the late ’s dr cornwall left academics for a nine year “sabbatical” to become the cofounder and presidentceo of atlantic behavioral health systems headquartered in raleigh nc  dr cornwall has received national awards for his work in curriculum development and teaching and in  he was named the national entrepreneurship educator of the year by the united states association of small business and entrepreneurship  he has published nine books and numerous articles on entrepreneurship  his blog the entrepreneurial mind is among the most popular with a focus on small business and entrepreneurship  the entrepreneurial mind is part of the forbes blog network and was named by that magazine as a “best of the web” it is also syndicated by the christian science monitor and many other outlets    antonio montoyafounder rocket hatchantonio is a serial immigrant and entrepreneur he has lived in europe south america and the caribbean but has called huntsville home since  he started his first business in college with his computer science professor developing software  his second venture a gis consulting practice took him to the caribbean and central and south america in  he moved to miami where he joined the dot com boom and sold high tech solutions to latin america  antonio relocated to huntsville to join the global product management team at intergraph now part of hexagon and later established and grew the local office for one of the leading geospatial services firms in north america where he was also head of marketing and demand generation programsantonio is committed to grow the startup community in north alabama in  antonio founded rocket hatch wwwrockethatchorg to promote and support local entrepreneurs and he serves on huntsvilles council on innovation and entrepreneurship reporting to mayor tommy battle antonio has been cofounder board member and advisor to several earlystage companies and consults with tech startups at wwwantoniomontoyacom  michael d shmerlingchairman choice food group inc and xmi holdings inc mr shmerling is a native nashvillian and a  graduate of the university of oklahoma where he earned a bachelor of accountancy degree  he began his career as a certified public accountant now “inactive” with the nashville office of ernst  young formerly ernst  ernst cpas  mr shmerling currently serves as the chairman of choice food group inc and xmi holdings incmr shmerling has founded or cofounded five businesses since leaving the practice of public accounting four of which were ultimately sold to publicly traded nyse or nasd companies  he has received numerous nashville business journal future  – as well as inc  awards for companies in which he was involved  in addition to this recognition he received the tennessee society of cpas – outstanding cpa in business and industry award in    in  he was awarded united way’s alexis de tocqueville society public service awardmr shmerling currently serves on the boards of nonprofits community foundation of middle tennessee abe’s garden nashville area chamber of commerce and chairs the tpac foundation  he is currently a member of two public company boards – renasant bank rnst and healthstream inc hstm – and serves on the audit committee of each incrowd insider newsletter sign up below to receive a monthly curation of our favorite angel and venture blogs articles and other educational content  happy learning first name last name email address sign up thank you michael shmerling  choice food group inc  zoominfocomaffordable apartments planned off charlotte avenuesubscribe nowto get full accessget the newslog in or subscribe to skipalready a subscriberlog insubscribe today for full access on your desktop tablet and mobile devicesubscribe nowalready a subscriber but dont have a loginactivate your digital access  share this storylet friends in your social network know what you are reading aboutfacebookemailtwittergooglelinkedinpinterestaffordable apartments planned off charlotte avenueshmerling family seek rezoning of site at pearl and fisk streets to allow  onebedroom units in two multifamily buildingspost to facebookaffordable apartments planned off charlotte avenue shmerling family seek rezoning of site at pearl and fisk streets to allow  onebedroom units in two multifamily buildings check out this story on tennesseancom httptnnewskrkab  cancelsendsenta link has been sent to your friends email addressposteda link has been posted to your facebook feed  join the conversationto find out more about facebook commenting please read the conversation guidelines and faqssubscribe todaylog insubscribed but dont have a loginactivate your digital accessaffordable apartments planned off charlotte avenuegetahn ward gwardtennesseancom published  pm ct jan    updated  am ct jan  two multifamily buildings would be built in the area behind the parking garage of the youth opportunity center on charlotte avenue which houses nonprofit groups such as oasis centerphoto submittedstory highlightsshmerling family seeks rezoning of site at pearl and fisk streets to allow  onebedroom units 